{"id": 2935, "source": "pestle", "subject": "physics", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2021", "session": "21N", "subtopic": "4-5-standing-waves", "title": "21N.1.SL.TZ0.17", "topic_id": "4", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>A string is fixed at both ends. P and Q are two particles on the string.</p>\n<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/></p>\n<p>The first harmonic standing wave is formed in the string. What is correct about the motion of P and Q?</p>\n<p><br/>A.  P is a node and Q is an antinode.</p>\n<p>B.  P is an antinode and Q is a node.</p>\n<p>C.  P and Q oscillate with the same amplitude.</p>\n<p>D.  P and Q oscillate with the same frequency.</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}